metadata.desc: Add the binary string data (the NULL value \0 is permitted) to the output queue of the socket socket in. metadata.desc: Bind a socket to a particular endpoint. This is somewhat similiar to "listening" for a connection. The endpoint string specifies the protocol and the port to accept connection from. nodes.VIPath: E:\LabVIEW\32-bit\LabVIEW 2020\vi.lib\addons\zeromq\zmq_socket.vi

metadata.desc: Create a socket of flavour socket type in context ctx in and linger time linger milliseconds (time permitted after zmq_term to finish queued operations). Note that ZeroMQ creates sockets with infinite linger (ZMQ_LINGER) by default, which is undesirable in a managed environment like LabVIEW since it hangs the parent process. But set it to -1 should infinite linger be required. Detailed API documentation: http://api.zeromq.org/3-2:zmq-socket
